# Tooling Prompts

Reference these prompts using: `@prompt-library/workspace-config/tooling prompt-name`

## Configure ESLint

**Use when:** Setting up or updating ESLint configuration

```
Configure ESLint following workspace standards:
1. Use Next.js ESLint config as base
2. Add workspace-standard rules (consistent with existing apps)
3. Configure for TypeScript and React
4. Set up proper ignore patterns (.next, node_modules, etc.)
5. Ensure compatibility with Prettier (no conflicting rules)
6. Add workspace-specific custom rules if needed
7. Configure for Next.js specific patterns
8. Match patterns from existing apps (Feedric/.eslintrc.json)
9. Verify linting works correctly with workspace code patterns
10. Test linting on sample files

Ensure ESLint and Prettier work together without conflicts.
```

