10. Ensure consistent formatting across workspace

Reference existing apps (.prettierrc files) for standard formatting rules.
```

## Configure Testing

**Use when:** Setting up Vitest or Jest with workspace patterns

```
Configure testing framework following workspace standards:
1. Set up Vitest configuration (vitest.config.ts) or Jest (jest.config.js)
2. Configure test file patterns (*.test.ts, *.spec.ts)
3. Set up test environment (jsdom for React components, node for API tests)
4. Configure coverage reporting
5. Set up test utilities and helpers
6. Configure path aliases for tests (@/*, etc.)
7. Add test scripts to package.json (test, test:run, test:watch)
8. Match patterns from existing apps (Feedric/vitest.config.ts)
9. Verify tests can import workspace modules correctly
10. Create example test file to verify setup

Use Vitest for new projects (preferred). Jest is acceptable for existing projects.
```

## Configure Git Hooks

**Use when:** Setting up Husky and git hooks

```
Set up Husky and git hooks following workspace standards:
1. Install Husky as a dev dependency
2. Initialize Husky (npx husky install)
3. Set up pre-commit hook (run lint-staged or lint before commit)
4. Set up pre-push hook (run tests before push, optional)
5. Configure lint-staged if using (format and lint staged files)
6. Add prepare script to package.json (husky install)
7. Verify git hooks work correctly
8. Test hooks with sample commits
9. Document git hooks setup in README
10. Ensure hooks don't slow down development workflow

Reference existing apps for git hooks patterns.
```

